Description: Fragment of oval handle from neck join to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with helios head symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '1.9̣' Name Symmachos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR P.16305, as is an example in Milan from Crocodilopolis.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (247)
